com.metrics.common.calculator

Class CreditCurve

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.metrics.common.mapping.SearchAdapter
      • com.metrics.common.calculator.CreditCurve
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.metrics.common.jobcontrol.IMarketEventListener

    public class CreditCurve
extends SearchAdapter
implements com.metrics.common.jobcontrol.IMarketEventListener
    Represent spreads relative to a reference yield curve against which securities are valued (yield = reference + spread + delta), where yield = yield from reference curve, spread = value from credit curve, and delta = security-specific adjustment. STORAGE Credit curves are stored as collections of Items (one Item per node). Curves include an integer version number to identify each collection. LIFE CYCLE A credit curve may be created at any time by introducing a collection of Items onto a server (Items must include required tags enumerated below, including an identifier indicating that a collection describes one and only one CreditCurve). A server-side daemon will periodically check for new CreditCurves or proposed updates to existing CreditCurves (see #CreditCurveManager); when discovered, new CreditCurves will be added to the actively managed list of CreditCurves while proposed updates will be validated and processed against existing CreditCurves. Once discovered, CreditCurves will receive automatic updates if qualifying market events occur following each CreditCurve's updatetime (the daemon manages retrieval of all active CreditCurves and will store updated versions of CreditCurves that change owing to qualified market events). Stale credit curves are deleted by the daemon. MARKET DATA REQUESTS A CreditCurve will add (but never remove) market data requests. This constraint prevents multiple curves from removing common requests registered with a single market data provider. To manage the total set of outstanding requests, periodically re-start the process that creates and manages CreditCurve objects.
